# Testing Rule — Quality Gates

Generated code must include tests appropriate to the change.

## Minimum expectations
- utilities: unit tests
- services: unit tests and/or integration tests
- APIs: contract/integration tests
- critical user journeys: e2e tests

## Priority user flows
- sign in
- create project
- create agent/app
- save configuration
- deploy
- view deployment status
- access published route

## Test qualities
- tests should be deterministic
- avoid brittle selectors in e2e
- avoid excessive mocking when integration tests are more valuable
- cover validation and authorization failures

## Forbidden patterns
- merging critical backend code with zero tests
- snapshot-heavy frontend testing without behavioral assertions
- fake passing tests that do not assert meaningful behavior
